Calderon May Propose Spending Decrease for 2012, Reforma Says

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-08-10T15:00:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/calderon-may-propose-spending-decrease-for-2012-reforma-says.html
Mexico ’s government may propose
lower spending and forecast slower economic growth for 2012
compared with 2011, newspaper Reforma  reported , citing a
lawmaker it didn’t identify.  Mexican Finance Minister  Ernesto Cordero  told lawmakers
yesterday that the ministry is working to reduce the budget
figures due to the global financial turbulence, according to the
Mexico City-based newspaper.  The lower house of congress must approve the income portion
of the budget by Oct. 31 and the spending portion by Nov. 15.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  